  }, "Recall - Out of all the positive outcomes in the truth set, how many got a positive test result?")), mdx("p", null, "From these definitions, we can see sensitivity and recall are the same thing with a different name!\nMany other popular metrics are aliases or easily derived from these definitions, such as positive predictive value (precision), true positive rate (sensitivity or recall), true negative rate (specificity) and false positive rate (1 - specificity).\nIn all such cases the four basic statistics are the rates of true and false, negatives and positives."), mdx("h2", {
